                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>فضیلت نامه</p>
                            <p>This MS. was bought from J. J. Naaman on May 7, 1903, for £4, and is
                                described under the heading "(25) C. 11 (Turkish)" in Further Notes, pp. 31-32
                                (563-564). It contains a Turkish mathnawi poem in the hexameter Hazaj metre,
                                chiefly in praise of 'Alí, by a poet who uses the pen-name of Yamíní. This poem
                                fills ff. 1-229, and was copied in Sha'bán, 1218/end of 1803. It is followed by
                                other poems by Shaykh-oghlu, Nasímí, etc. (ff. 230b-262b).</p>
                            <p>Ff. 262 of 19.8 x 14 c. and 17 ll.; bad ta'liq with rubrications within gold
                                margins.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="E_16-item1">
                            <locus from="1" to="229">ff. 1-229</locus>
                            <author key="">
                                <persName xml:lang="tr">Yamíní</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota">یمینی</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ota">فضیلت نامه</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x" key="">Fadílat-náma</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">Turkish mathnawi poem in the
                                hexameter Hazaj metre, chiefly in praise of 'Alí</title>
